gomodel:SYNGO_5108  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: DHHC5 specifically binds and palmitoylates GRIP1 (pulldowns for various mutants in HEK293T cells).\n\nFigure 2a,b: synaptic localization of DHHC5 was shown by co-localization with Bassoon (BSN) in immunofluorescence imaging of primary hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 2c: in biochemical fractions, DHHC5 was enriched in PSD fractions.\n\nFigure 2g,h: DHHC5 Palmitoylated GRIP1 in primary neurons.. Experimental description: mice were used in these experiments, although not explicitly mentioned. To confirm mouse protein sequence annotation is valid, M&M confirms that the HA-tagged sequences were from mouse; \"HA-tagged mouse DHHC5 and DHHC8 and mycHis-tagged human DHHC8 cDNA have been previously described (Fukata et al, 2004; Ohno et al., 2006).\"\n\nantibody:\nDHHC5 (Sigma), ZDHHC8 (Everest Biotech)\n\nshRNA knockdown:\nshRNAs (in vector pLKO; Mission shRNA library) targeting sequences identical in both rat and mouse DHHC5 (5'-CCTCAGATGATTCCAAGAGAT-3') or DHHC8 (5'-CTTCAGTATGGCTACCTTCAT-3') were tested for their ability to reduce expression of HA-tagged DHHC5 and DHHC8 mouse cDNAs in cotransfected HEK293T cells." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5108" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

